5-Fold Cross Validation Performances¶

In [1]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

# Load the data
df = pd.read_excel('All metrics_set6.xlsx')

# Define colors for each group
group_colors = {
    'tree': 'lightcoral',
    'bagging': 'lightseagreen',
    'boosting': 'cornflowerblue',
    'other': 'goldenrod'
}

# Map group colors to the DataFrame
df['color'] = df['group'].map(group_colors)

# Set figure size
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

# Create a horizontal bar plot with colored bars
bars = plt.barh(df['algorithm'], df['cv_accuracy_mean'], color=df['color'])

# Add finer error bars for cv_accuracy_std
plt.errorbar(
    df['cv_accuracy_mean'], 
    df['algorithm'], 
    xerr=df['cv_accuracy_std'], 
    fmt='none', 
    ecolor='black', 
    elinewidth=0.8,  # Thinner error bar line
    capsize=3,       # Smaller caps
    capthick=0.8,    # Thinner cap line
    alpha=0.7        # Slight transparency for a finer look
)

# Define an offset for the labels
label_offset = 0.055 * df['cv_accuracy_mean'].max()  # Adjust offset as needed

# Add value labels on the right side of each bar, with offset to avoid error bars
for idx, value in enumerate(df['cv_accuracy_mean']):
    plt.text(value + label_offset, idx, f'{value:.2f}', va='center', ha='left', fontsize=10)

# Add labels and title
plt.xlabel('Accuracy Scores')
plt.title('5-Fold Cross Validation Accuracy Scores')

# Adjust x-axis limits to add padding on the right
plt.xlim(0, df['cv_accuracy_mean'].max() + label_offset * 2)

# Invert the Y-axis to have the highest scores at the top
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()

# Display the plot
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from math import pi

# Increase font sizes globally
plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 12})  # Adjust the number to increase/decrease

# Load data 
df = pd.read_excel('All metrics_set6.xlsx')

# Normalize data using Min-Max scaling
def min_max_scale(series):
    return (series - series.min()) / (series.max() - series.min())

df_norm = df.copy()
df_norm['cv_accuracy_mean'] = min_max_scale(df['cv_accuracy_mean'])
df_norm['cv_f1_mean'] = min_max_scale(df['cv_f1_mean'])
df_norm['cv_auc_mean'] = min_max_scale(df['cv_auc_mean'])  
df_norm['cv_recall_mean'] = min_max_scale(df['cv_recall_mean'])
df_norm['cv_precision_mean'] = min_max_scale(df['cv_precision_mean'])

# Set up the radar chart
labels = np.array(df['algorithm'])
num_vars = len(labels)

# Compute angle each axis is centered on
angles = np.linspace(0, 2 * pi, num_vars, endpoint=False).tolist()
angles += angles[:1]  # Complete the loop

# Plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8), subplot_kw=dict(polar=True))

# Draw one line per metric with individual scales
# cv_accuracy_mean
values = df_norm['cv_accuracy_mean'].tolist()
values += values[:1]
ax.plot(angles, values, linewidth=1.5, linestyle='solid', label='Normalized Accuracy Score')
ax.fill(angles, values, 'b', alpha=0.2)

# cv_f1_mean
values = df_norm['cv_f1_mean'].tolist()
values += values[:1]
ax.plot(angles, values, linewidth=1.5, linestyle='solid', label='Normalized F1 Score')
ax.fill(angles, values, 'r', alpha=0.2)

# cv_AUC_mean
values = df_norm['cv_auc_mean'].tolist()
values += values[:1]
ax.plot(angles, values, linewidth=1.5, linestyle='solid', label='Normalized AUC Score')
ax.fill(angles, values, 'purple', alpha=0.2)

# cv_recall_mean
values = df_norm['cv_recall_mean'].tolist()
values += values[:1]
ax.plot(angles, values, linewidth=1.5, linestyle='solid', label='Normalized Recall Score')
ax.fill(angles, values, 'o', alpha=0.2)

# cv_precision_mean
values = df_norm['cv_precision_mean'].tolist()
values += values[:1]
ax.plot(angles, values, linewidth=1.5, linestyle='solid', label='Normalized Precision Score')
ax.fill(angles, values, 'g', alpha=0.2)

# Add labels
ax.set_xticks(angles[:-1])
ax.set_xticklabels(labels, ha='center', position=(-0.25, -0.25))  # Position labels farther away

# Adjust distance of radial labels from the center
ax.set_rlabel_position(235)  # Angle position for radial labels

# Add legend
plt.ylim(0, 1)
plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.8, 1.1))

plt.show()
